         <div type="commentary" subtype="linebyline">
            <list>
               <item corresp="#div1-lb3" xml:space="preserve">
            <ref>2</ref>
            <p>
              νυποεπακ could be a new adjective ὑποέπακρος, similar to ἔπακρος ('sharp, pointy') used by Hippocrates to define a kind of μότοι ('tampons'): cf.
              <emph rend="italics">Morb.</emph>
              2.61.3 (7, 96.4 L).
            </p>
          </item>
               <item corresp="#div1-lb7" xml:space="preserve">
            <ref>6</ref>
            <p>
              ἀποδορά ('peeling of the skin') according to Nicole is an hapax.
              <emph rend="italics">Contra</emph>
              Marganne cf. Agathin.
              <emph rend="italics">ap.</emph>
              Orib.,
              <emph rend="italics">Coll.med.</emph>
              10.7.18 (CMG 6.1.2, 51.20-2 Raed.).
            </p>
          </item>
               <item corresp="#div1-lb14" xml:space="preserve">
            <ref>13</ref>
            <p>
              διαρραφή ('sewing up') is attested in Sor. 3.40.2 (CMG 4, 119.9-10 Ilberg) only; for use of διαρράπτω ('sew through') cf. Gal.
              <emph rend="italics">In Hipp.Off.Med.comment.</emph>
              2.8 (18B 746.1 K); Archig.
              <emph rend="italics">ap.</emph>
              Orib.,
              <emph rend="italics">Coll.med.</emph>
              47.13.5 (CMG 7.2.1, 257.20-2 Raed.).
            </p>
          </item>
               <item corresp="#div1-lb16" xml:space="preserve">
            <ref>15</ref>
            <p>
              ῥάμμα ('fastening by sewing, suture') cf. Hp.
              <emph rend="italics">Off.</emph>
              8 (3, 294.6-296.1-2 L); Dsc.
              <emph rend="italics">Eup.</emph>
              1.200.3 (3, 227.25 W); Gal.
              <emph rend="italics">In Hipp.Off.Med.comment.</emph>
              2.7 (18B 740.10-4 K) and II 10 (18B 752.3-5 K).
            </p>
          </item>
               <item corresp="#div1-lb17" xml:space="preserve">
            <ref>16</ref>
            <p>
              διαφερομένου ('pushed through') cf. Hp.
              <emph rend="italics">Edip.</emph>
              5.21 (5, 220.14-5 L).
            </p>
          </item>
               <item corresp="#div1-lb18" xml:space="preserve">
            <ref>17</ref>
            <p>
              ἐπιβολάς means here 'sewing two edges of a wound'; cf. Gal.
              <emph rend="italics">meth.med.</emph>
              6.6 (10, 452.16 K); Aret. 3.8.6 (CMG 2, 48.24-5 Hude).
            </p>
          </item>
               <item corresp="#div1-lb21" xml:space="preserve">
            <ref>20</ref>
            <p>abbreviations β’ and α’ correspond, according to Nicole, to δισσῶς and πρῶτον respectively.</p>
          </item>
            </list>
